## **Quick Setup Commands**

To quickly create all these files, you can run:

```bash
# Create directory structure
mkdir -p EventRegistrationApp
cd EventRegistrationApp

# Create all files
echo "<App.js content>" > App.js
echo "<RegistrationForm.js content>" > RegistrationForm.js
echo "<Confirmation.js content>" > Confirmation.js
echo "<package.json content>" > package.json
echo "<README.md content>" > README.md
echo "<.gitignore content>" > .gitignore

# Initialize git and push
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit: Event Registration App"
git remote add origin https://github.com/ewuwise/EventRegistrationApp.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```

**Note:** Replace `<file content>` with the actual code from above for each file.

This gives you a complete, working React Native Event Registration App ready to be deployed 
